quran[64]{c,v,t}:
  84,1,When the universe is ripped apart
  84,2,"And it listens to its Guardian Evolver, as it must"
  84,3,And when the earth is flattened out
  84,4,And casts up what is within it and becomes empty
  84,5,"And listens to its Lord, as it must"
  84,6,"O human beings, indeed you are toiling on towards your Lord, ever toiling, but you will meet Him"
  84,7,Then he who is given his record in his right hand
  84,8,Soon his account will be taken by an easy reckoning
  84,9,And he will turn to his people rejoicing
  84,10,But he who is given his record behind his back
  84,11,Soon he will cry for perdition
  84,12,And he will enter a blazing fire
  84,13,"Indeed he went about among his people, rejoicing"
  84,14,Indeed he thought that he would not have to return to Us
  84,15,"No, no, for his Lord was watchful of him"
  84,16,So I call to witness the ruddy glow of sunset
  84,17,The night and its homing
  84,18,And the moon in its fullness
  84,19,You will surely travel from stage to stage
  84,20,What then is the matter with them that they do not believe
  84,21,"And when the Quran is read to them, they do not fall prostrate"
  84,22,But instead the unbelievers reject it
  84,23,But God has full knowledge of what they hide
  84,24,So announce to them a terrible penalty
  84,25,"Except to those who believe and do righteous deeds, for them is a reward that will never fail"
  85,1,"By the sky, displaying the constellations"
  85,2,By the promised day
  85,3,"By one who witnesses, and the subject of the witness"
  85,4,Woe to the makers of the pit
  85,5,The fire supplied with fuel
  85,6,"Behold, they sat over against the fire"
  85,7,And they witnessed all that they were doing against the believers
  85,8,"And they treated them wrongfully for no other reason than that they believed in God, the All Mighty, the Praiseworthy"
  85,9,"Him to Whom belongs the control of the heavens and the earth, and God is witness to all things"
  85,10,"Those who persecute or draw into temptation the believers, men and women, and do not turn in repentance, will have the penalty of hell. They will have the penalty of the burning fire"
  85,11,"For those who believe and do righteous deeds, will be gardens with rivers flowing through them. That is the great salvation"
  85,12,Truly strong is the Grip of your Lord
  85,13,It is He Who originates and repeats
  85,14,"And He is the Oft-Forgiving, Full of Loving-Kindness"
  85,15,Lord of the throne of glory
  85,16,Doer of all that He intends
  85,17,"Has the story reached you, of the forces"
  85,18,Of Pharaoh and the Thamud
  85,19,And yet the unbelievers persist in rejecting
  85,20,But God encompasses them from behind
  85,21,"No, this is a glorious Quran"
  85,22,On material preserved
  86,1,By the galaxy and the night visitant
  86,2,And what will explain to you what the night-visitant is
  86,3,It is the star of piercing brightness
  86,4,There is no soul that does not have a protector over it
  86,5,Now let the human being think about from what he is created
  86,6,He is created from a drop emitted
  86,7,Proceeding from between the backbone and the ribs
  86,8,Surely God is able to bring him back
  86,9,The day that all things secret will be tested
  86,10,They will have no power and no helper
  86,11,By the firmament which returns
  86,12,And by the earth which cracks open
  86,13,Behold this is the word that is decisive
  86,14,It is not a thing for entertainment
  86,15,"As for them, they are plotting a scheme"
  86,16,But I am devising a plan
  86,17,Therefore grant respite to the unbelievers. Give respite to them for a while